VSo I've been thinking about the difference between
p4
aVthe résumé virtues and  the eulogy virtues.
p5
aVThe résumé virtues are the ones you put on your résumé,
p6
aVwhich are the skills  you bring to the marketplace.
p7
aVThe eulogy virtues are the ones
p8
aVthat get mentioned in the eulogy,
p9
aVwhich are deeper: who are you,  in your depth,
p10
aVwhat is the nature of your relationships,
p11
aVare you bold, loving, dependable, consistency?
p12
aVAnd most of us, including  me, would say
p13
aVthat the eulogy virtues are the more important of the virtues.
p14
aVBut at least in my case,  are they the ones that
p15
aVI think about the most?  And the answer is no.
