VI was reminded of a common response through history
p74
aVof how you build a solid Adam II,
p75
aVhow you build a depth of character.
p76
aVThrough history, people  have gone back
p77
aVinto their own pasts,
p78
aVsometimes to a precious  time in their life,
p79
aVto their childhood,
p80
aVand often, the mind  gravitates in the past
p81
aVto a moment of shame,
p82
aVsome sin committed,  some act of selfishness,
p83
aVan act of omission, of shallowness,
p84
aVthe sin of anger, the sin of self-pity,
p85
aVtrying to be a people-pleaser,  a lack of courage.
p86
aVAdam I is built by  building on your strengths.
p87
aVAdam II is built by fighting  your weaknesses.
